               National Institute of Standards and Technology
                      POSTDOCTORAL RESEARCH ASSOCIATES*
                      in Ceramic Science and Technology

                                Eligibility:
                              Doctoral Degree
                               US citizenship
                                 Location:
                              Gaithersburg, MD
                                 Duration:
                            Two-Year Appointment
                                  Stipend:
                       $50,000 + annual allocation of
                   $5,500 to support professional travel,
                  books, miscellaneous research equipment
                                 Benefits:
                  Relocation expenses to Gaithersburg, MD,
           Government health, life insurance, and retirement plan

                                    Examples of Topical Areas:
                * Mechanisms of Brittle Failure
                * Simulation and Modeling
                * Nanotribology
                * Reliability of Films and Coatings
                * Processing Measurements
                * X-ray methods - Development and Use
                * Phase Equilibria - Theory and Experiment
                * Ceramics for Wireless

              Deadline for Research Proposals: January 15, 2001
                      For further information Contact:
                Dr. Stephen Freiman, Chief, Ceramics Division
                         Gaithersburg, MD 20899-8520
                  Telephone: 301/975-6119 FAX: 301/975-5334
                      E-mail: stephen.freiman@nist.gov

